data.title: Justified City Primeval episode 1: All episodes release date, time, where to stream
data.meta_description: "Justified: City Primeval" is a thrilling miniseries sequel with Timothy Olyphant as Raylan Givens, facing off against Boyd Holbrook's menacing sociopath in Detroit.
data.text:
Synopsis

"Justified: City Primeval" is a thrilling miniseries sequel with Timothy Olyphant as Raylan Givens, facing off against Boyd Holbrook's menacing sociopath in Detroit.

In the eagerly awaited miniseries "Justified: City Primeval", Timothy Olyphant plays renowned lawman Raylan Givens, who makes a dramatic comeback in a gripping Western-style thriller. The series, which is based on Elmore Leonard's "City Primeval: High Noon in Detroit," picks up fifteen years after Raylan departed Kentucky and places him in Detroit where he must contend with Boyd Holbrook's menacing sociopath portraying The Oklahoma Wildman.

If you enjoyed the original "Justified" series, which is presently available to stream on Hulu, you'll enjoy this sophisticated sequel. "Justified: City Primeval" is a riveting experience that is comparable to enjoying a cold drink of bourbon on a hot summer day. You can view the miniseries online at the following link.

Justified City Primeval Release Date:

On Tuesday, July 18 at 10:00 pm (ET) on FX, the much anticipated miniseries debuts. The first two episodes will be broadcast consecutively from 10:00 p.m. to 12:28 am (ET), with the encore presentation taking place from 12:28 am to 2:57 am (ET).

Justified City Primeval Episodes:

"Justified: City Primeval" consists of eight thrilling episodes.

Where to Watch Justified City Primeval:

If you have a valid cable login, you can watch "Justified: City Primeval" on FX.com. Additionally, you can stream FX live by subscribing to fuboTV, Hulu + Live TV, YouTube TV, or Sling TV.

Free trials are available for YouTube TV and fuboTV for new subscribers.

Justified City Primeval Streaming on Hulu:

"Justified: City Primeval" episodes will be available for next-day streaming on Hulu. Starting Wednesday, July 19, you can catch the first two episodes on the platform.

Cast Information:

In addition to Timothy Olyphant's reprisal of the iconic Raylan Givens, "Justified: City Primeval" features a talented cast including Aunjanue Ellis as Carolyn Wilder, Adelaide Clemens as Sandy, Vondie Curtis Hall as Sweety, Marin Ireland as Maureen, Norbert Leo Butz as Norbert, and Victor Williams as Wendall.

Two intriguing details regarding the cast: Boyd Holbrook plays Clement Mansel, also referred to as The Oklahoma Wildman, who serves as the season's main antagonist. In addition, Vivian Olyphant, who is Timothy Olyphant's real-life daughter, portrays his fictional daughter Willa Givens.

Take a thrilling journey into the world of law enforcement and the pursuit of justice as "Justified: City Primeval" transports you there with its intense grip.

Guide to all episodes of "Justified: City Primeval"

Episode 1 of "City Primeval" will air on Tuesday, July 18 on FX.

Episode 2 of "The Oklahoma Wildman" will air on the same day.

Episode 3 of "Backstabbers" will air on Tuesday, July 25 on FX.

Episode 4: "Kokomo" will debut on FX on Tuesday, August 1;

episode 5: "You Good?" - On FX starting Tuesday, August 8

Episode 6: "Adios" debuts on Tuesday, August 15 on FX.

Episode 7: The Smoking Gun" premieres on Tuesday, August 22 on FX.

Episode 8: "The Question" debuts on Tuesday, August 29 on FX.

FAQs

Q1: What is "Justified: City Primeval"?

A1: "Justified: City Primeval" is a gripping miniseries sequel to the original "Justified." It follows the renowned lawman Raylan Givens, played by Timothy Olyphant, as he makes a dramatic comeback in Detroit after fifteen years.

Q2: How many episodes are there in "Justified: City Primeval"?

A2: "Justified: City Primeval" consists of eight thrilling episodes. Stream on FX.com or catch it on Hulu from July 19.
